---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro"
---

<Layout title="ATS Score Checker | Free Resume Builder" description="Check your resume's ATS compatibility score for free. Optimize your resume for Applicant Tracking Systems with our AI-powered analysis.">
  <div style="max-width:960px;margin:0 auto;padding:3rem 1.25rem">
    <div style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:2.5rem">
      <h1 style="font-size:2.25rem;font-weight:800;color:var(--gray-900);margin-bottom:0.75rem;letter-spacing:-0.02em">ATS Resume Score Checker</h1>
      <p style="font-size:1.0625rem;color:var(--gray-500);max-width:640px;margin:0 auto">Analyze your resume for Applicant Tracking System compatibility. Get a detailed score and actionable tips to improve your chances.</p>
    </div>

    <div id="ats-app" style="max-width:720px;margin:0 auto">
      <div class="card" style="padding:1.5rem">
        <div style="margin-bottom:1rem">
          <label class="label">Paste Your Resume Content</label>
          <textarea id="resume-text" class="input" rows="10" style="font-size:0.875rem;line-height:1.6;font-family:inherit" placeholder="Paste your full resume text here...">Sarah Johnson
sarah.johnson@email.com | +1 (555) 987-6543 | New York, NY
linkedin.com/in/sarahjohnson

PROFESSIONAL SUMMARY
Creative product designer with 6+ years of experience crafting user-centered digital experiences. Proficient in design thinking, prototyping, and design systems.

EXPERIENCE
Senior Product Designer | DesignStudio Co | Mar 2021 - Present
- Led redesign of core product, improving user engagement by 35%
- Established design system used by 12 product teams
- Conducted 50+ user research sessions to inform product decisions

UI/UX Designer | WebAgency | Jun 2018 - Feb 2021
- Designed and shipped 20+ client websites and mobile apps
- Reduced design-to-dev handoff time by 40% through improved workflows

EDUCATION
Bachelor of Fine Arts, Graphic Design | Rhode Island School of Design | 2014 - 2018

SKILLS
Design: Figma, Sketch, Adobe XD, Prototyping
Research: User Research, Usability Testing, Data Analysis</textarea>
        </div>
        <div style="display:flex;gap:0.75rem;align-items:flex-end;margin-bottom:1rem">
          <div style="flex:1">
            <label class="label">Target Job Title (optional)</label>
            <input id="job-title" class="input" type="text" placeholder="e.g. Product Designer" value="Product Designer" />
          </div>
          <button id="check-btn" class="btn btn-primary" style="padding:0.5rem 1.5rem;height:38px" onclick="checkATS()">
            <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="9 11 12 14 22 4"/><path d="M21 12v7a2 2 0 01-2 2H5a2 2 0 01-2-2V5a2 2 0 012-2h11"/></svg>
            Check Score
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div id="results" style="display:none"></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div style="max-width:960px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 1.25rem 4rem">
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(200px,1fr));gap:1rem;margin-bottom:4rem">
      <div class="card" style="padding:1.25rem">
        <div style="width:36px;height:36px;border-radius:8px;background:var(--primary-light);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;margin-bottom:0.75rem">
          <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--primary)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="9 11 12 14 22 4"/><path d="M21 12v7a2 2 0 01-2 2H5a2 2 0 01-2-2V5a2 2 0 012-2h11"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3 style="font-size:0.9375rem;font-weight:600;color:var(--gray-900);margin-bottom:0.375rem">Instant Analysis</h3>
        <p style="font-size:0.8125rem;color:var(--gray-500);line-height:1.5">Get your ATS score in seconds. Paste your resume and see results immediately.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="padding:1.25rem">
        <div style="width:36px;height:36px;border-radius:8px;background:var(--primary-light);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;margin-bottom:0.75rem">
          <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--primary)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 20V10"/><path d="M18 20V4"/><path d="M6 20v-4"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3 style="font-size:0.9375rem;font-weight:600;color:var(--gray-900);margin-bottom:0.375rem">Detailed Breakdown</h3>
        <p style="font-size:0.8125rem;color:var(--gray-500);line-height:1.5">Score across 5 categories: keywords, bullets, headers, contact, and formatting.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="padding:1.25rem">
        <div style="width:36px;height:36px;border-radius:8px;background:var(--primary-light);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;margin-bottom:0.75rem">
          <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--primary)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M12 16v-4"/><path d="M12 8h.01"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3 style="font-size:0.9375rem;font-weight:600;color:var(--gray-900);margin-bottom:0.375rem">Actionable Tips</h3>
        <p style="font-size:0.8125rem;color:var(--gray-500);line-height:1.5">Get specific, prioritized recommendations to improve your score fast.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="padding:1.25rem">
        <div style="width:36px;height:36px;border-radius:8px;background:var(--primary-light);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;margin-bottom:0.75rem">
          <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--primary)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="2" y="3" width="20" height="14" rx="2" ry="2"/><line x1="8" y1="21" x2="16" y2="21"/><line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12" y2="21"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3 style="font-size:0.9375rem;font-weight:600;color:var(--gray-900);margin-bottom:0.375rem">100% Free</h3>
        <p style="font-size:0.8125rem;color:var(--gray-500);line-height:1.5">No sign-up, no limits. Your resume data never leaves your browser.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <article style="color:var(--gray-600);font-size:0.9375rem;line-height:1.8">
      <h2 style="font-size:2rem;font-weight:800;color:var(--gray-900);margin-bottom:1.25rem;letter-spacing:-0.02em;line-height:1.3">What Is an ATS Resume Score?</h2>
      <p style="font-size:1.0625rem;color:var(--gray-500);margin-bottom:2rem;line-height:1.7">An ATS (Applicant Tracking System) is software that companies use to screen resumes before a human ever sees them. Your ATS score measures how well your resume is optimized for these systems. A higher score means your resume is more likely to pass automated screening and reach a recruiter's desk.</p>

      <h3 style="font-size:1.25rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--gray-900);margin:2.5rem 0 1rem;letter-spacing:-0.01em">How the ATS Score Is Calculated</h3>
      <p>Our ATS checker analyzes five key areas: <strong>Keyword Match</strong> compares your resume against industry-specific keywords for your target role. <strong>Bullet Quality</strong> evaluates whether you use action verbs and quantified achievements. <strong>Section Headers</strong> checks for standard, parsable section headings. <strong>Contact Info</strong> verifies your email, phone, and LinkedIn are present. <strong>Formatting</strong> detects tables, complex layouts, and date consistency. Each category is weighted to produce a final 0-100 score.</p>

      <h3 style="font-size:1.25rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--gray-900);margin:2.5rem 0 1rem;letter-spacing:-0.01em">Tips to Improve Your ATS Score</h3>
      <p>Start by tailoring your resume to each job description — mirror the keywords used in the posting. Use strong action verbs like "Led," "Developed," and "Implemented" to start every bullet point. Quantify your achievements with percentages, dollar amounts, and timeframes. Stick to standard section headers (Experience, Education, Skills). Avoid tables, columns, images, and graphics. Keep your resume to 1-2 pages. Finally, save and submit your resume as a .docx or plain text — some ATS systems struggle with PDFs.</p>

      <p style="margin-top:2rem">Once you know your score, use our <a href="/" style="color:var(--primary);text-decoration:none;font-weight:500">free resume builder</a> to rewrite weak sections, or browse <a href="/resume-examples" style="color:var(--primary);text-decoration:none;font-weight:500">resume examples</a> for inspiration in your industry.</p>
    </article>
  </div>

  <div style="background:var(--gray-50);border-top:1px solid var(--gray-200);border-bottom:1px solid var(--gray-200);padding:3rem 1.5rem">
    <div style="max-width:960px;margin:0 auto">
      <h3 style="font-size:1.125rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--gray-900);margin-bottom:1.25rem;text-align:center">Free Career Tools</h3>
      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(130px,1fr));gap:0.75rem">
        <a href="/" class="card card-hover" style="padding:1rem;text-decoration:none;display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;text-align:center">
          <span style="width:36px;height:36px;border-radius:8px;background:var(--primary-light);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center">
            <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--primary)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v16a2 2 0 002 2h12a2 2 0 002-2V8z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/></svg>
          </span>
          <span style="font-size:0.8125rem;font-weight:600;color:var(--gray-700)">Resume Builder</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/ats-score" class="card card-hover" style="padding:1rem;text-decoration:none;display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;text-align:center">
          <span style="width:36px;height:36px;border-radius:8px;background:var(--primary-light);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center">
            <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--primary)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="9 11 12 14 22 4"/><path d="M21 12v7a2 2 0 01-2 2H5a2 2 0 01-2-2V5a2 2 0 012-2h11"/></svg>
          </span>
          <span style="font-size:0.8125rem;font-weight:600;color:var(--gray-700)">ATS Score</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/cover-letter" class="card card-hover" style="padding:1rem;text-decoration:none;display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;text-align:center">
          <span style="width:36px;height:36px;border-radius:8px;background:var(--primary-light);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center">
            <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--primary)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M4 4h16c1.1 0 2 .9 2 2v12c0 1.1-.9 2-2 2H4c-1.1 0-2-.9-2-2V6c0-1.1.9-2 2-2z"/><polyline points="22,6 12,13 2,6"/></svg>
          </span>
          <span style="font-size:0.8125rem;font-weight:600;color:var(--gray-700)">Cover Letter</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/resume-examples" class="card card-hover" style="padding:1rem;text-decoration:none;display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;text-align:center">
          <span style="width:36px;height:36px;border-radius:8px;background:var(--primary-light);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center">
            <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--primary)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="11" cy="11" r="8"/><line x1="21" y1="21" x2="16.65" y2="16.65"/></svg>
          </span>
          <span style="font-size:0.8125rem;font-weight:600;color:var(--gray-700)">Examples</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/templates" class="card card-hover" style="padding:1rem;text-decoration:none;display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;text-align:center">
          <span style="width:36px;height:36px;border-radius:8px;background:var(--primary-light);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center">
            <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--primary)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="2" ry="2"/><line x1="3" y1="9" x2="21" y2="9"/></svg>
          </span>
          <span style="font-size:0.8125rem;font-weight:600;color:var(--gray-700)">Templates</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#2563eb,#1d4ed8);padding:3rem 1.5rem;text-align:center">
    <div style="max-width:480px;margin:0 auto">
      <h3 style="font-size:1.375rem;font-weight:800;color:white;margin:0 0 0.5rem;letter-spacing:-0.02em">Get Weekly Resume Tips</h3>
      <p style="font-size:0.9375rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.8);margin:0 0 1.25rem">Join 10,000+ job seekers getting expert advice straight to their inbox.</p>
      <form id="email-form" style="display:flex;gap:0.5rem;max-width:400px;margin:0 auto" onsubmit="event.preventDefault();var e=document.getElementById('email-input');if(e.value){alert('Thanks for subscribing!');e.value=''}">
        <input type="email" id="email-input" placeholder="your@email.com" style="flex:1;border-radius:8px;border:none;padding:0.625rem 0.875rem;font-size:0.875rem;font-family:inherit;box-shadow:0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.05)" required />
        <button type="submit" style="border-radius:8px;border:none;background:#0f172a;color:white;padding:0.625rem 1.25rem;font-size:0.875rem;font-weight:600;cursor:pointer;font-family:inherit;transition:all 0.15s;box-shadow:0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.1)" onmouseover="this.style.opacity='0.9';this.style.transform='translateY(-0.5px)'" onmouseout="this.style.opacity='1';this.style.transform='translateY(0)'">Subscribe</button>
      </form>
      <p style="font-size:0.6875rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.4);margin:0.625rem 0 0">No spam. Unsubscribe anytime.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    const ACTION_VERBS = ["achieved","administered","analyzed","architected","built","chaired","coached","collaborated","consolidated","created","cultivated","decreased","delivered","designed","developed","devised","directed","doubled","drove","edited","eliminated","enabled","engineered","established","evaluated","exceeded","expanded","expedited","generated","grew","hired","identified","implemented","improved","increased","initiated","innovated","integrated","introduced","invented","launched","led","managed","mentored","mitigated","negotiated","optimized","organized","overhauled","pioneered","proposed","prototyped","provided","reduced","reengineered","reorganized","resolved","restructured","revamped","reviewed","revised","saved","simplified","solved","spearheaded","standardized","streamlined","strengthened","structured","supervised","surpassed","systemized","transformed","upgraded"]

    const INDUSTRY_KEYWORDS = {
      "product designer": ["user research", "wireframe", "prototype", "figma", "sketch", "usability", "design system", "user testing", "ux", "ui", "interaction design", "responsive", "accessibility", "a/b testing", "persona", "user flow", "information architecture", "mockup", "design thinking", "visual design"],
      "software engineer": ["javascript", "python", "java", "react", "node", "api", "backend", "frontend", "full stack", "database", "sql", "aws", "docker", "kubernetes", "microservices", "testing", "ci/cd", "agile", "git", "rest", "graphql", "typescript", "algorithm", "system design"],
      "data scientist": ["machine learning", "python", "r", "tensorflow", "pytorch", "sql", "statistics", "regression", "classification", "nlp", "deep learning", "data pipeline", "etl", "visualization", "a/b testing", "pandas", "numpy", "feature engineering", "model deployment"],
      "marketing manager": ["seo", "sem", "content marketing", "social media", "analytics", "campaign", "brand", "conversion", "crm", "email marketing", "google ads", "facebook ads", "roi", "kpi", "market research", "growth", "strategy", "budget management"],
      "project manager": ["agile", "scrum", "jira", "stakeholder", "risk management", "budget", "timeline", "sprint", "waterfall", "pmp", "cross-functional", "resource allocation", "milestone", "gantt", "retrospective"],
      "graphic designer": ["photoshop", "illustrator", "indesign", "typography", "branding", "logo design", "print", "layout", "color theory", "adobe creative suite", "visual identity", "packaging design", "motion graphics"],
    }

    function getKeywordsForRole(title) {
      const lower = title.toLowerCase()
      for (const [role, keywords] of Object.entries(INDUSTRY_KEYWORDS)) {
        if (lower.includes(role)) return keywords
      }
      return ["experience", "team", "project", "management", "skills", "communication", "leadership", "strategy", "development", "analysis"]
    }

    function countOccurrences(text, keywords) {
      const lower = text.toLowerCase()
      let found = 0; const foundKeywords = []
      for (const kw of keywords) {
        if (lower.includes(kw)) { found++; foundKeywords.push(kw) }
      }
      return { found, total: keywords.length, foundKeywords }
    }

    function countBullets(text) {
      const matches = text.match(/^[-•*]\s+/gm) || text.match(/^\d+\.\s+/gm) || text.match(/\n\s*[-•]\s/g)
      return matches ? matches.length : 0
    }

    function countQuantified(text) {
      const lines = text.split("\n").filter(l => l.trim().startsWith("-") || l.trim().startsWith("•") || l.trim().startsWith("*"))
      if (!lines.length) return 0
      const withNumbers = lines.filter(l => /\d+%|\d+x|\$\d+|\d+\s+(users|clients|customers|projects|team|members|reports|sales)/i.test(l))
      return Math.round((withNumbers.length / lines.length) * 100)
    }

    function countActionVerbsUsed(text) {
      const lower = text.toLowerCase()
      const lines = text.split("\n").filter(l => l.trim().startsWith("-") || l.trim().startsWith("•") || l.trim().startsWith("*"))
      if (!lines.length) return 0
      const withAction = lines.filter(l => ACTION_VERBS.some(v => new RegExp("^[-•*]\\s*" + v, "i").test(l.trim())))
      return Math.round((withAction.length / lines.length) * 100)
    }

    function checkDateConsistency(text) {
      const datePatterns = text.match(/\b(Jan|Feb|Mar|Apr|May|Jun|Jul|Aug|Sep|Oct|Nov|Dec)[a-z]*\s+\d{4}\b/g) ||
                          text.match(/\b\d{4}\s*[-–]\s*\d{4}\b/g) ||
                          text.match(/\b\d{4}\s*[-–]\s*(Present|Current|Now)\b/gi)
      return datePatterns && datePatterns.length >= 2 ? 100 : datePatterns && datePatterns.length >= 1 ? 50 : 0
    }

    function generateTips(checks, score) {
      const tips = []
      if (score < 30) tips.push("Your resume needs major improvements. Start by adding standard section headers like 'Experience' and 'Education'.")
      if (!checks.hasEmail) tips.push("Add your email address - it's the most common way recruiters contact you.")
      if (!checks.hasPhone) tips.push("Include a phone number so hiring managers can reach you quickly.")
      if (!checks.hasLinkedIn) tips.push("Add your LinkedIn profile URL. 87% of recruiters use LinkedIn to vet candidates.")
      if (checks.bulletCount < 30) tips.push("Add more bullet points in your experience section. Aim for 3-5 per role with specific achievements.")
      if (checks.quantified < 40) tips.push(`Only ${checks.quantified}% of your bullets have numbers. Use metrics: "Increased sales by 30%" beats "Helped increase sales."`)
      if (checks.actionVerbs < 50) tips.push(`Only ${checks.actionVerbs}% of your bullets start with strong action verbs. Use words like "Led", "Developed", "Implemented".`)
      if (!checks.hasExperience) tips.push('Add an "Experience" or "Work History" section - it\'s the most important section for ATS parsing.')
      if (!checks.hasEducation) tips.push('Include an "Education" section with your degrees and institutions.')
      if (!checks.hasSkills) tips.push('Add a "Skills" section with relevant technical and professional skills.')
      if (checks.keywordMatch < 40) tips.push(`Your resume matches only ${checks.keywordMatch}% of expected keywords. Study the job description and incorporate missing terms.`)
      if (checks.wordCount > 800) tips.push("Your resume is too long. Keep it to 1-2 pages (400-800 words).")
      if (checks.wordCount < 200) tips.push("Your resume is too short. Add more details about your experience and achievements.")
      if (tips.length === 0) tips.push("Excellent! Your resume looks well-optimized for ATS. Keep tailoring it for each application.")
      return tips.slice(0, 6)
    }

    function checkATS() {
      const text = document.getElementById("resume-text").value
      const title = document.getElementById("job-title").value || ""
      const results = document.getElementById("results")

      if (!text.trim()) {
        results.style.display = "block"
        results.innerHTML = `<div class="card" style="padding:1.5rem;margin-top:1.5rem;border-left:4px solid var(--error);background:#fef2f2"><p style="color:var(--error);font-weight:600;font-size:0.9375rem">Please paste your resume content to check your ATS score.</p></div>`
        return
      }

      const wordCount = text.split(/\s+/).length
      const bulletCount = countBullets(text)
      const quantified = countQuantified(text)
      const actionVerbs = countActionVerbsUsed(text)
      const keywords = getKeywordsForRole(title || "software engineer")
      const kwMatch = countOccurrences(text, keywords)
      const hasEmail = /\S+@\S+\.\S+/.test(text) ? 100 : 0
      const hasPhone = /[\+]?[\d\-\(\)\s]{10,}/.test(text) ? 100 : 0
      const hasLinkedIn = /linkedin\.com/.test(text) ? 100 : 0
      const hasExperience = /experience|work history|employment/i.test(text) ? 100 : 0
      const hasEducation = /education|academic|university|college|school|bachelor|master|phd/i.test(text) ? 100 : 0
      const hasSkills = /skills|technologies|competencies|expertise/i.test(text) ? 100 : 0
      const hasSummary = /summary|objective|profile|about me/i.test(text) ? 100 : 0
      const noTables = /<table/i.test(text) ? 30 : 100
      const dates = checkDateConsistency(text)

      const contactScore = Math.round((hasEmail + hasPhone + hasLinkedIn) / 3)
      const headersScore = Math.round((hasExperience + hasEducation + hasSkills + hasSummary) / 4)
      const bulletScore = Math.round(Math.min(100, (bulletCount / 40) * 100) * 0.4 + quantified * 0.3 + actionVerbs * 0.3)
      const lengthScore = Math.round(Math.min(100, (wordCount / 600) * 100) * (wordCount <= 800 ? 1 : wordCount > 1000 ? 0.5 : 0.8))
      const formatScore = Math.round((noTables + dates) / 2)
      const keywordMatch = Math.round((kwMatch.found / kwMatch.total) * 100)
      const score = Math.round(contactScore * 0.10 + headersScore * 0.15 + bulletScore * 0.25 + lengthScore * 0.10 + formatScore * 0.10 + keywordMatch * 0.30)

      const tips = generateTips({
        hasEmail: hasEmail > 0, hasPhone: hasPhone > 0, hasLinkedIn: hasLinkedIn > 0,
        hasExperience: hasExperience > 0, hasEducation: hasEducation > 0,
        hasSkills: hasSkills > 0, hasSummary: hasSummary > 0,
        bulletCount, quantified, actionVerbs, wordCount, keywordMatch
      }, score)

      const scoreColor = score >= 75 ? "var(--success)" : score >= 50 ? "var(--warning)" : "var(--error)"
      const scoreLabel = score >= 90 ? "Excellent" : score >= 75 ? "Good" : score >= 50 ? "Needs Work" : "Poor"
      const circumference = 2 * Math.PI * 54
      const offset = circumference - (score / 100) * circumference

      results.style.display = "block"
      results.innerHTML = `
        <div class="card" style="padding:1.5rem;margin-top:1.5rem">
          <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:240px 1fr;gap:1.5rem;align-items:center">
            <div style="text-align:center">
              <svg width="130" height="130" viewBox="0 0 120 120">
                <circle cx="60" cy="60" r="54" fill="none" stroke="var(--gray-200)" stroke-width="8"/>
                <circle cx="60" cy="60" r="54" fill="none" stroke="${scoreColor}" stroke-width="8" stroke-linecap="round"
                  stroke-dasharray="${circumference}" stroke-dashoffset="${offset}" transform="rotate(-90 60 60)"/>
                <text x="60" y="52" text-anchor="middle" font-size="28" font-weight="800" fill="var(--gray-900)">${score}</text>
                <text x="60" y="74" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="600" fill="${scoreColor}">${scoreLabel}</text>
              </svg>
              <div style="font-size:0.6875rem;color:var(--gray-400);margin-top:0.375rem">${wordCount} words · ${bulletCount} bullets</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 style="font-size:1rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--gray-900);margin-bottom:0.75rem">Score Breakdown</h3>
              <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.5rem">
                <div><div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;font-size:0.75rem;margin-bottom:0.125rem"><span style="color:var(--gray-500)">Keyword Match</span><span style="font-weight:600;color:var(--gray-700)">${keywordMatch}%</span></div><div style="height:6px;background:var(--gray-100);border-radius:3px;overflow:hidden"><div style="height:100%;width:${keywordMatch}%;background:${keywordMatch >= 70 ? "var(--success)" : keywordMatch >= 40 ? "var(--warning)" : "var(--error)"};border-radius:3px;transition:width 0.6s"></div></div></div>
                <div><div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;font-size:0.75rem;margin-bottom:0.125rem"><span style="color:var(--gray-500)">Bullet Quality</span><span style="font-weight:600;color:var(--gray-700)">${bulletScore}%</span></div><div style="height:6px;background:var(--gray-100);border-radius:3px;overflow:hidden"><div style="height:100%;width:${bulletScore}%;background:${bulletScore >= 70 ? "var(--success)" : bulletScore >= 40 ? "var(--warning)" : "var(--error)"};border-radius:3px;transition:width 0.6s"></div></div></div>
                <div><div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;font-size:0.75rem;margin-bottom:0.125rem"><span style="color:var(--gray-500)">Section Headers</span><span style="font-weight:600;color:var(--gray-700)">${headersScore}%</span></div><div style="height:6px;background:var(--gray-100);border-radius:3px;overflow:hidden"><div style="height:100%;width:${headersScore}%;background:${headersScore >= 70 ? "var(--success)" : headersScore >= 40 ? "var(--warning)" : "var(--error)"};border-radius:3px;transition:width 0.6s"></div></div></div>
                <div><div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;font-size:0.75rem;margin-bottom:0.125rem"><span style="color:var(--gray-500)">Contact Info</span><span style="font-weight:600;color:var(--gray-700)">${contactScore}%</span></div><div style="height:6px;background:var(--gray-100);border-radius:3px;overflow:hidden"><div style="height:100%;width:${contactScore}%;background:${contactScore >= 70 ? "var(--success)" : contactScore >= 40 ? "var(--warning)" : "var(--error)"};border-radius:3px;transition:width 0.6s"></div></div></div>
                <div><div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;font-size:0.75rem;margin-bottom:0.125rem"><span style="color:var(--gray-500)">Formatting</span><span style="font-weight:600;color:var(--gray-700)">${formatScore}%</span></div><div style="height:6px;background:var(--gray-100);border-radius:3px;overflow:hidden"><div style="height:100%;width:${formatScore}%;background:${formatScore >= 70 ? "var(--success)" : formatScore >= 40 ? "var(--warning)" : "var(--error)"};border-radius:3px;transition:width 0.6s"></div></div></div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          ${tips.length ? `
            <div style="border-top:1px solid var(--gray-100);margin-top:1.25rem;padding-top:1.25rem">
              <h4 style="font-size:0.875rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--gray-900);margin-bottom:0.75rem">${tips.length} Ways to Improve Your ATS Score</h4>
              <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.5rem">
                ${tips.map((tip, i) => `<div style="display:flex;gap:0.5rem;align-items:flex-start;padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;background:var(--gray-50);border-radius:var(--radius-sm)"><span style="font-size:0.75rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--primary);flex-shrink:0;width:20px;height:20px;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;background:var(--primary-light);border-radius:999px">${i+1}</span><span style="font-size:0.8125rem;color:var(--gray-600)">${tip}</span></div>`).join("")}
              </div>
            </div>
          ` : ""}
          <div style="border-top:1px solid var(--gray-100);margin-top:1.25rem;padding-top:1.25rem;text-align:center">
            <p style="font-size:0.8125rem;color:var(--gray-500);margin-bottom:0.75rem">Want to improve your score? Use our resume builder to rewrite weak sections.</p>
            <div style="display:flex;gap:0.75rem;justify-content:center;flex-wrap:wrap">
              <a href="/" class="btn btn-primary btn-sm" style="text-decoration:none">Edit Resume in Builder</a>
              <a href="/resume-examples" class="btn btn-outline btn-sm" style="text-decoration:none">View Resume Examples</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      `
    }
  </script>
</Layout>